Hysteria sighed deeply, so much for leaving. She stood behind Kluster 
while he talked with Phobia. Her eyes nervously darted around the 
room. Her beastmode was uncomfortable around lions, and it was 
effecting her logic circuits. Still, she would be alright, she just 
had to keep her beastmode under control.

>

here 
to help 
> the Maximals."
> 
> He turns serious. "Down to buisness," he says, turning to Phobia, 
"What's 
> this info you wanted to share with us, and why is it worth risking 
being 
> scrapped by both us and the predacons, when they find out you 
betrayed them?"
